import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over the years?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.scatter(data['wages'], data['wheat'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Wages')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wages and wheat production?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['wheat'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['wheat'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['wheat'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of wheat production?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Wheat Production")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wages'] = data['wages'].astype(float)
    avg_wages = data.groupby('year')['wages'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_wages['year'], avg_wages['wages'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=avg_wages['wages'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Wage')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Wages')
    ax.set_title('What is the average wage per year?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.set_index('year')
    corr = data.corr()
    sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between wheat production and wages?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
